<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: Pharmaceutical shares catch a nasty
cold - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pharmaceutical stocks, for a long time the glamour boys of the stock market,
have taken a beating in recent months. The plans of President Bill Clinton
and his wife to reform the US healthcare sector started the rot, but the UK
giants have had suffered setbacks of their own. Glaxo saw the departure of
its chief executive; and this week Wellcome shares suffered from a report
questioning the efficacy of its anti-AIDS drug, AZT. These stocks were
trading on such high price-earnings ratios that bad news was bound to have a
disproportionate effect on their prices.
</TEXT>
