<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / UK Company News: SelecTV director survives investigation
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RAYMOND SNODDY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR ALLAN McKeown, the controversial managing director of SelecTV, the
independent production company, has survived an investigation by the
company's solicitors, Richards Butler.
The solicitors were asked to conduct a detailed investigation following the
issuing of a writ last month against Mr McKeown alleging irregularities in
the way the company was run. The writ was never served.
SelecTV, which makes programmes such as Lovejoy and Birds of a Feather, said
last night it would issue a full statement to the Stock Exchange on Monday
giving the results of the Richards Butler review.
It is clear that, following the investigation, Mr McKeown will be fully
reinstated with the support of the SelecTV board.
The company is, however, expected to take note of points made about its
standards of corporate governance.
</TEXT>
