<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Economic Diary
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
TODAY: Mr William Clinton, US president, and Mr Boris Yeltsin, Russian
leader, hold their first summit in Vancouver. Labour Party Women's
conference in Llandudno (until Sunday).
MONDAY: Cyclical indicators for the UK economy (February-first estimate).
Credit business (February). London sterling certificates of deposit (April).
Monetary statistics (including bank and building society balance sheets;
bank and building society sterling lending and M4 sectoral analysis)
(February). Bill turnover statistics (February). Sterling commercial paper
(February). Money market statistics (February). European Community foreign
ministers meet in Luxembourg to discuss planned co-operation accord with
Russia and hold formal start of negotiations to admit Norway (until April
6). European Community internal market ministers meet in Luxembourg.
European Community social affairs ministers meet in Luxembourg to discuss
draft directives on working hours and on posting workers abroad. General
Motors Corporation board meeting. Preliminary figures announced by Mirror
Group Newspapers and Morgan Crucible. Royal Society of Chemistry holds
annual congress in Southampton (until Thursday).
TUESDAY: German unemployment figures (March). Mr William Clinton, US
president, meets Mr Hosni Mubarak, Egyptian president, in Washington.
Preliminary figures from Tesco.
WEDNESDAY: Credit business (February). Advance energy statistics (February).
Ballot closes in Aslef train drivers' vote on industrial action over planned
sell-off of BR. CBI issues statement. Mr John Patten, education secretary,
addresses Association of Teachers and Lecturers conference in Cardiff. Start
of Cambodian election campaign.
THURSDAY: Details of employment, unemployment, earnings, prices and other
indicators. Census of employment (1991). US producer prices (March); capital
spending (fourth quarter). Fokker shareholders meet to vote on DASA merger.
</TEXT>
