<TEXT>
Sir, How appropriate that your leader, 'Local councils', appeared on April
Fool's Day.
The London borough of Haringey informed me the previous day that my council
tax bill for 1993-94 is Pounds 1048.05. In 1992-93 the community charge for
my wife and myself, the only residents at the address below, totalled Pounds
767.84. The increase is Pounds 270.21 - which is considerably more than the
maximum weekly figure Pounds 3.50 given by your writer.
Neither my wife nor I would grudge paying more in order to improve the
educational and library services as well as seeing that there is, for a
change, adequate resources made available for care in the community.
