<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / EC backs Red Hot TV ban
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW HILL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE European Commission yesterday backed the British government's plan to
outlaw Red Hot Television, a pornographic television channel transmitted
into the UK, Andrew Hill writes.
Mr Joao de Deus Pinheiro, the EC commissioner for audiovisual policy, said
the measures outlined by the UK were compatible with EC law and Brussels
would not be raising any objections.
Red Hot Television, originally called Red Hot Dutch, is thought to be
transmitted via satellite from Denmark, and is received by subscribers using
decoders sold under licence from a Dutch-registered channel.
The commission said it was unable to confirm where the broadcaster was
established, or which member state had jurisdiction over the channel.
But Mr Pinheiro said member states were obliged to take action against
broadcasts which 'might impair the physical, mental or moral development of
minors, in particular those that involve pornography or gratuitous
violence'.
