<HEADLINE>
FT  03 APR 93 / Imports ban after cattle tested
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
IMPORTS OF cattle from the Czech and Slovak republics were banned by the
Ministry of Agriculture yesterday after positive tests for foot and mouth
disease. The ban also applies to pigs, deer, sheep, goats and other
susceptible cloven-hoofed animals.
There have been 51 outbreaks of the disease in Italy this year, with eastern
Europe suspected as the source, and thousands of animals have been
slaughtered.
The ministry said the positive tests did not necessarily indicate that
animals were infected, as those vaccinated against the disease showed a
similar reaction.
