<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / UK Company News: Stratagem raises Harrison holding
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Stratagem, the investment group, has acquired a further 1.19m shares in
Harrison Industries, the doors and castings supplier, at 4.1p per share from
Mr Ken Harrison, former chairman, and his family.
Stratagem has also been granted an option to acquire a further 28.81m shares
from the family at the same price, exercisable on April 6. If this option is
exercised, the total consideration payable to the family would amount to
Pounds 1.23m.
Stratagem already owns 1.18m Harrison shares and following completion of the
latest transactions would own an aggregate 31.18m shares, representing some
25.1 per cent of the issued capital.
