<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / International Company News: Pak Suzuki reduces loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FARHAN BOKHARI
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ISLAMABAD
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PAK Suzuki Motors, the Karachi-based car maker in which Suzuki Motor of
Japan holds 40 per cent, has reported a reduced net loss of Rs71m (Dollars
2.68m) for the first half to the end of December, from Rs170m a year
earlier, writes Farhan Bokhari in Islamabad. The result is the first since
the company was privatised last summer.
Pre-tax losses fell to Rs78m from Rs159m on turnover 14 per cent lower at
Rs2.48bn compared with Rs2.14bn.
Suzuki produces Pakistan's smallest and most popular car. The business
received a boost last year when Mr Nawaz Sharif, Pakistan prime minister,
ordered a nationwide loan scheme to help the unemployed buy Suzuki taxis.
