FT  02 APR 93 / International Company News: Axa planning more funds for The
Equitable
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
AXA, the French insurance company, is planning to make another Dollars 300m
capital injection in The Equitable, the large but troubled US life insurer,
it was announced late yesterday in New York.
Axa injected Dollars 1bn into the ailing insurance and financial services
group in 1991, receiving a 49 per cent stake in The Equitable when the US
group converted from mutual status to a shareholder-owned company last year.
Axa's new investment comes as part of a Dollars 600m fund-raising exercise
by The Equitable, designed to bolster the capital base of its life insurance
subsidiaries. The US insurer said that it planned to sell this amount of
convertible securities via a private placement. The nature of the
convertible securities was not specified, but The Equitable said they would
swap into about 25m shares of common stock after July 22 1994.
'Axa is expected to purchase 49 per cent of the convertible securities,'
said The Equitable. The remaining securities, it added, were expected to go
to institutional investors.
