FT  02 APR 93 / UK Company News: Hong Kong disposal for Faupel Trading
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Faupel Trading Group, the USM-quoted textile importer, has sold Oriental
Finzel to its management for HKDollars 1 and the sale of certain
intellectual property rights for HKDollars 60,000 (Pounds 5,000).
These amounts will be added to the repayment of an intercompany loan account
which will total HKDollars 449,044. This sum will be capitalised as zero
coupon preference shares in Finzel which will be redeemed at par in 12
monthly instalments.
Finzel, acquired by Faupel in 1990, is based in Hong Kong and trades in
electrical and electronic components.
The disposal will result in an extraordinary charge of Pounds 233,000 in
Faupel's accounts for the year to March 31 1993. There will also be a Pounds
637,000 charge for goodwill previously written off to reserves. Faupel said
it was unlikely to maintain profits for the year, but intends to recommend
an unchanged final dividend.
