FT  02 APR 93 / International Company News: MGM reduces loss to Dollars
45.6m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN DICKSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
METRO-Goldwyn-Mayer, the Hollywood studio taken over by Credit Lyonnais, its
French bank creditor, reported a fourth-quarter net loss of Dollars 45.6m,
compared with Dollars 114.2m in the same period of 1991, and said the bank
had agreed to support its business plan, which calls for substantial new
film production, writes Martin Dickson in New York.
MGM had an operating loss for the period of Dollars 8.5m, down from Dollars
65.3m in 1991.
