dividend with effect from July 1 1992 to 5.9p, fixed preferred dividends of
4.9p were paid to preference shareholders.
The company said that it intended to move to a progressive dividend policy
'reflecting a level of payment and cover appropriate to LWT's performance
and cash position.'
LWT paid a relatively modest Pounds 7.58m bid to retain its London weekend
franchise.
The shares rose 23p to 378p.
