<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / UK Company News: Abbey National establishes mortgage
insurance offshoot
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER, Banking Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ABBEY NATIONAL, the mortgage lender, yesterday disclosed that it had
established a captive insurer to provide its mortgage indemnity insurance.
Abbey last month announced its intention to write its own mortgage indemnity
insurance.
It has established a subsidiary, Carfax Insurance, in Guernsey with working
capital of Pounds 10m. It will be managed by Willis Corroon Management.
Abbey was now starting talks with re-insurers. It was confident about the
outcome, and there was no question of returning to previous arrangements for
mortgage cover, held with a panel of insurers.
The move marks the first break with traditional insurers by a large mortgage
lender as a result of the re-negotiation of mortgage indemnity terms over
the past year. Insurers have both raised rates and made terms more
restrictive.
Mr John Bayliss, deputy chairman, said the company had been offered terms
which were 1.5 times as expensive by its panel of insurers and which
provided only 65 per cent of the cover under traditional mortgage indemnity
terms.
He said Abbey would not charge its traditional commission on mortgage
indemnity cover payments made by borrowers, and therefore the amount
available to provide cover on its properties would rise by 30 per cent.
'This will give us a competitive edge because we will be able to look at our
own book and possessions and balance our cover. It will be cheaper in the
long term,' he said.
Mr Bayliss said that Carfax could be made into a close company in two or
three years time if a foreign insurance company entered the British scene
offering better terms than the traditional mortgage insurers.
A number of building societies have also made inquiries about establishing
captive insurers to replace traditional contracts. But they are limited
because they are barred from owning more than 15 per cent of a non-life
insurer.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Abbey National.
    Carfax Insurance.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P6351 Surety Insurance.
    P6021 National Commercial Banks.
</IN>
<XX>
Types:-
</XX>
