<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / UK Company News: Revamped Boustead incurs Pounds 49,000 loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BOUSTEAD, the industrial products and technical services group acquired last
year by Jack Chia-MPH, the Singapore-based trading company, yesterday
reported full year results which reflected tough trading conditions and the
impact of a wide-ranging restructuring.
After Jack Chia-MPH acquired its controling 74.77 per cent interest a new
management team undertook restructuring aimed at streamlining the group's
structure, improving its business focus, reducing gearing and lowering the
cost base.
Costs associated with the restructuring led to a Pounds 49,000 pre-tax loss
in 1992 compared with a Pounds 886,000 profit.
Turnover edged ahead to Pounds 78.1m (Pounds 76.5m).
After a Pounds 975,000 (Pounds 1.64m) extraordinary charge to cover the
closure of two Singapore businesses and costs of the change in control, and
'exceptionally high' tax charges of Pounds 1.09m (Pounds 480,000), losses
per share were 1.6p, compared to earnings of 0.6p.
However, the final dividend is held at a recommended 0.35p, maintaining the
total for the year at 0.7p.
In Singapore a number of businesses which did not fit the new strategy were
sold or closed last year, reducing the number of businesses there from 31 to
11.
In the UK, following business sales and mergers, the group is now focused on
the manufacture of industrial products for European markets in two main
business areas, automotive components and cleaning equipment.
Since the year-end the group has sold another two businesses in Singapore
and one in the UK for a total of Pounds 8.9m, bringing overall proceeds from
disposals to Pounds 12.9m.
These funds have mainly been used to strengthen the balance sheet.
If all the disposals had been completed by the year-end the group would have
had net cash of Pounds 2.9m and shareholders funds of Pounds 20.5m.
The group is changing its financial year-end to March 31 to conform with
Jack Chia-MPH's accounting year.
