<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / US group to spend Dollars 6bn on three gas plants
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DEBORAH HARGREAVES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ENRON, one of the largest gas companies in the US, expects to announce plans
to build at least three gas-fired power stations worldwide by the end of the
year - one in the UK - at a total cost of close to Dollars 6bn (Pounds
4.2bn).
The company yesterday inaugurated its 1,875MW power plant at Teesside which
is the largest combined heat and power station in the world.
Mr Ken Lay, chairman and chief executive of Enron, said the Teesside plant
in which the company owns a 50 per cent stake will be a showpiece for its
worldwide power operations. The Teesside station cost Pounds 850m and took
just over two years to build, which the company believes is the shortest
construction time ever for a plant of this size.
Mr Lay said the company was in discussions about a Dollars 600m gas-fired
power plant in Kuwait and a Dollars 2bn power project in Turkey, where it is
working with Midlands Electricity which also has a stake in Teesside. Enron
is also negotiating with India about a Dollars 3bn complex south of Bombay.
Mr Lay stressed that Enron would not be investing the full cost of these
plants because the company did not plan to take more than a half share in
each venture and all would be funded by project finance.
'Our vision is to become the world's first global gas integrated company
capable of developing projects in any segment of the gas business like the
oil majors 50 years ago,' he said. Mr Lay believes that gas will become a
more important fuel than oil early next century.
In the UK, he said the company was involved in detailed discussions about
three or four new gas-fired stations, one of which he expected to go ahead
with by the end of the year at a probable cost of about Dollars 400m.
Enron is finalising a Dollars 200m project for Russia's Gazprom to update
part of its pipeline system and compressor stations. The company is also
talking to China about setting up a joint venture to construct a 2,000MW to
4,000MW power station at a cost of between Dollars 2bn and Dollars 4bn.
Enron transports about 18 per cent of US gas usage through its pipelines and
had a turnover of Dollars 6.33bn last year. It operates four gas-fired power
stations in the US with another under construction.
