<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Observer: High flown
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
True, there could be no fitter quotation to mark the start of the Royal Air
Force's 76th year than Churchill's 'Never in the field of human conflict was
so much owed by so many to so few'. There is, however, another that military
policy-makers in particular would do well to remember.
It was uttered by Field Marshal Sir William Nicholson, chief of the imperial
general staff just seven years before the RAF was formed, and went:
'Aviation is a useless and expensive fad advocated by a few individuals
whose ideas are unworthy of attention.'
</TEXT>
