<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Observer: By appointment
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
What would Sir Adrian Cadbury say about Queens Moat, whose shares have been
suspended since Wednesday?
On paper QM would seem to be following best practice on the corporate
governance front. It has an audit and remuneration committee which is
chaired by a non-executive director - Maurice Hart - who is also an
accountant. However, Hart, who has been associated with the group since
1968, was formerly senior partner of Bird Luckin, Queens Moat's relatively
unknown chartered accountants. A review of Bird Luckin's clients shows it
has a single listed company - yup, you guessed it. Queens Moat.
</TEXT>
<XX>
