<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Observer: Rest uneasy
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Times get even tougher at Mirror Group Newspapers, wracked by sackings and
resignations since Ulster hardman David Montgomery arrived as chief
executive. During London's last rail strike, journalists were put up at
hotels.
This time, the demoralised hacks have been offered camp beds in the office.
