FT  02 APR 93 / Letter: Saving for retirement should be encouraged
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr PAUL SWAIN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, It is important to provide the answer - cut from my original letter
(March 27) - to my rhetorical question on life insurance. In the context of
the high cost of selling life insurance I asked: 'Why not simply leave the
customer alone to buy or not buy if he feels the urge?' The point is
received wisdom has it that the urge will be unfelt and the product
unbought. While this would not matter if the product were a video recorder
or a box of cornflakes, given the probable collapse of the state pension
scheme it is important the public be encouraged to save for the unexpected
and retirement.
Paul Swain,
10 Granville Square,
London WC1X 9PF
</TEXT>
