<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Technology: World's smallest instant camera - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The world's smallest instant camera is how Polaroid describes Vision, a
folding camera with a window on the back through which the photographer can
see the developing picture.
Polaroid has shrunk the camera by incorporating the functions carried out by
seven chips into a single micro-controller. The in-built flash emits a brief
range-finding beam as the shutter release is pressed, to determine the
distance of the object while the micro-controller calculates the best
exposure from information on ambient and infra-red light. The picture size
has also shrunk. The cost of each photo is Pounds 1. Polaroid: UK, 0727
859191.
</TEXT>
