FT  02 APR 93 / Technology: Giving computer staff a boost - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
With the proliferation of personal computers the role of the traditional
data processing department is increasingly coming under scrutiny.
One particular problem, says Bob Zawacki, professor of management and
international business at the University of Colorado, is that computer staff
are highly motivated, but poor at the social skills needed to handle
customers.
Zawacki's research is being used by KPMG Management Consulting as a basis
for its People Performance service, which aims to improve the performance of
computer staff by up to 30 per cent by assessing their performance against a
list of indicators. KPMG: UK, 071 236 8000.
