FT  02 APR 93 / Technology: Cut-price ways with training videos - Worth
Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Expensive in-house training videos have been one of the first casualties of
recessionary cuts. Now a desk-top editing system could reinstate videos at
considerably less expense.
Developed in the US, Media Suite Pro, from Avid Technology, works on an
Apple PC. The recorded film is digitised and transferred from the tape on to
a two-gigabyte disc, which can store up to 40 minutes of footage. Using a
mouse, the film editor can splice images together and add music or sound
using the computer keyboard. A package including Apple Mac, disc drive and
VCR costs Pounds 17,000. Avid: UK, 071 434 0122.
