<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / People: Departures
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Carl Young has resigned as finance director of BM Group, the troubled
construction equipment and engineering concern.
He had held the post since July 1988 when BM reorganised following the
acquisition of Tod and of Beazer Products and Services. Since then the group
acquired Blackwood Hodge in autumn 1990 and Thomas Robinson early last year.
His departure, to take place between now and June, is part of the shake-up
at BM after the collapse in its performance and share price triggered by the
departure of founding chairman Roger Shute last June.
BM, which made a record Pounds 34.6m pre-tax profit in 1991-92, announced
nearly Pounds 42m of restructuring costs and write-offs on Wednesday. It is
in discussions with its bankers over breaches of covenant and a programme of
debt reduction.
