<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Statement over Bank aid rejected
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE GOVERNMENT yesterday turned down Labour demands for a Commons statement
on last month's disclosure that a number of banks had received financial
support from the Bank of England in the second half of 1991, and that some
were still in receipt of Bank funds.
Mr Anthony Nelson, a junior Treasury minister, replied to a string of
written questions on the subject from Labour's Mr Alistair Darling by saying
it was for the Bank to determine its policy on answering questions
concerning such matters.
