<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / World Trade News: Swedish group signs new telecoms deal with
China
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
ERICSSON, the Swedish telecommunications group, yesterday signed a Dollars
300m contract for AXE switching equipment with China's Guangdong Post and
Telecommunications Bureau, its biggest ever contract in one of its fastest
growing markets.
The accord formalises a framework agreement reached last June.
The deal covers AXE-10 switching equipment, transmission and cooling
equipment which will be delivered from Sweden between 1993 and 1995.
Last year Ericsson signed framework agreements and memorandums of
understanding for more than Dollars 900m with China, which is now its eighth
largest market.
